FBIS3-15923 "drsov048_b_94020" FBIS-SOV-94-048 Document Type:Daily Report 11 Mar 1994 RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS Economic Issues Yeltsin Signs Edict on Tula Experimental Development LD1003171194 Moscow Mayak Radio Network in Russian 1200 GMT 10 Mar 94 LD1003171194 Moscow Mayak Radio Network Language: Russian Article Type:BFN [Text] Russian President Boris Yeltsin today signed a decree on holding an experiment in Tula Oblast to create organizational, legal, and economic conditions for the development of a regional agro-industrial complex, the presidential press service has reported. It is believed that the experiment will span the period between 1994 and 1998. It will be underpinned by economic self-management, expanded rights of the oblast authorities in implementing budgetary, investment, and credits policies, and also by improved internal production and economic relations.
